{"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GAppInfoMonitor"},{"text":" monitors application information for changes.","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"kind":"symbol","topicSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfoMonitorProtocol\/app_info_monitor_ptr-ma0f"],"title":"Instance Properties","anchor":"Instance-Properties"},{"generated":true,"title":"Instance Methods","anchor":"Instance-Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfoMonitorProtocol\/connect(signal:flags:data:destroyData:signalHandler:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfoMonitorProtocol\/connect(signal:flags:handler:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfoMonitorProtocol\/onChanged(flags:handler:)"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfoMonitorProtocol\/changedSignal"],"title":"Type Properties","generated":true,"anchor":"Type-Properties"}],"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"AppInfoMonitorProtocol","kind":"identifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ObjectProtocol","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B8ProtocolP"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"GAppInfoMonitor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is a very simple object used for monitoring the app"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"info database for changes (newly installed or removed applications)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Call [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.AppInfoMonitor.get"},{"text":"] to get a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GAppInfoMonitor"},{"text":" and connect","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to the [signal[AppInfoMonitor](\/\/documentation\/gio\/appinfomonitor\/onchanged(flags:handler:)] signal. The signal will be emitted once when","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the app info database changes, and will not be emitted again until after the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"next call to [func"},{"code":"Gio.AppInfo.get_all","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] or another "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_app_info_*()"},{"text":" function.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This is because monitoring the app info database for changes is expensive.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following functions will re-arm the [signal[AppInfoMonitor](\/\/documentation\/gio\/appinfomonitor\/onchanged(flags:handler:)]"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"signal so it can be emitted again:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"[func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.AppInfo.get_all"},{"text":"]","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.AppInfo.get_all_for_type"},{"text":"]","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"[func","type":"text"},{"code":"Gio.AppInfo.get_default_for_type","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.AppInfo.get_fallback_for_type"},{"text":"]","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"[func","type":"text"},{"code":"Gio.AppInfo.get_recommended_for_type","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"]","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"..\/gio-unix\/type_func.DesktopAppInfo.get_implementation.html","isActive":true}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"..\/gio-unix\/ctor.DesktopAppInfo.new.html","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"..\/gio-unix\/ctor.DesktopAppInfo.new_from_filename.html"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"..\/gio-unix\/ctor.DesktopAppInfo.new_from_keyfile.html","type":"reference"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"..\/gio-unix\/type_func.DesktopAppInfo.search.html","type":"reference","isActive":true}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The latter functions are available if using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"..\/gio-unix\/class.DesktopAppInfo.html","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gio-unix-2.0.pc"},{"type":"text","text":" (GIR namespace "},{"code":"GioUnix-2.0","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":").","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In the usual case, applications should try to make note of the change","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(doing things like invalidating caches) but not act on it. In"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"particular, applications should avoid making calls to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GAppInfo"},{"text":" APIs","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in response to the change signal, deferring these until the time that"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the updated data is actually required. The exception to this case is when"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"application information is actually being displayed on the screen","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(for example, during a search or when the list of all applications is shown).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"The reason for this is that changes to the list of installed applications"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"often come in groups (like during system updates) and rescanning the list"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"on every change is pointless and expensive.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfoMonitorProtocol","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying ","type":"text"},{"code":"GAppInfoMonitor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfoMonitor","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Alternatively, use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AppInfoMonitorRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" as a lighweight, "},{"code":"unowned","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO"]]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/appinfomonitorprotocol"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"AppInfoMonitorProtocol"}],"modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"externalID":"s:3GIO22AppInfoMonitorProtocolP","symbolKind":"protocol","roleHeading":"Protocol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"AppInfoMonitorProtocol"}],"title":"AppInfoMonitorProtocol","role":"symbol"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":